info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 19 at 6:06AM PST until November 19 at 11:00PM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...HIGH WIND WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH MONDAY EVENING... * WHAT...North winds 35 to 50 mph with gusts of 60 to 80 mph trough this evening, then northeast winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts to 60 mph possible late this evening through Monday evening. * WHERE...Southern Ventura County Mountains, Interstate 5 Corridor and Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor. * WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, until 11 PM PST this evening. For the High Wind Watch, from this evening through Monday evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. Travel will be difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around large trees. If possible, remain in your home and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
